claim.claim-text:
A map matching method (300) for a vehicle safety warning system (VSWS) (12), the method comprising:
determining (100) if intelligent transportation system (ITS) map data (18) is available;
determining (112) a vehicle location (30) and a vehicle heading (32);
determining (108) an envelope area (38) around a road feature (34) defined by the ITS map data (18);
determining (110) a segment heading (46) for a segment (36) of the road feature (34);
determining (120) a separation distance (50) between the vehicle location (30) and the segment (36) if (114,116,118) the vehicle location (30) is located within the envelope area (38), the segment heading (46) is substantially similar to the vehicle heading (32), and optionally, the segment elevation is substantially similar to the vehicle elevation; and
map matching (128) the vehicle location (30) to the segment (36) if (126) the separation distance (50) is less than a threshold.

A vehicle safety warning system (VSWS) (12) configured to be installed in a vehicle (10), said system comprising:
an intelligent transportation system (ITS) map receiver (20) configured to receive ITS map data (18);
a global positioning system (GPS) receiver (22) configured to determine a vehicle location (30) and a vehicle heading (32);
a controller (24) configured to a) receive the ITS map data (18) from the ITS map receiver (20), b) receive the vehicle location (30) and the vehicle heading (32) from the GPS receiver (22), c) determine an envelope area (38) around a road feature (34) defined by the ITS map data (18), d) determine a segment heading (46) for a segment (36) of the road feature (34), e) determine a separation distance (50) between the vehicle location (30) and the segment (36) if the vehicle location (30) is located within the envelope area (38), the vehicle heading (32) is substantially similar to the segment heading (46), and optionally, the vehicle elevation is substantially similar to the segment elevation, and f) map match the vehicle location (30) to the segment (36) if the separation distance (50) is less than a threshold.
